<li>Oct &#8217;25: New preprints available:
<ul>
<li>Z. Mei*, O. Shorinwa*, and A. Majumdar, <a href="https://www.arxiv.org/abs/2510.02571">&#8220;How Confident are Video Models? Empowering Video Models to Express their Uncertainty&#8221;</a></li>
<li>Z. Mei*, O. Shorinwa*, and A. Majumdar,  <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.03104">&#8220;Geometry Meets Vision: Revisiting Pretrained Semantics in Distilled Fields&#8221;</a></li>
<li>A. Badithela, D. Snyder, L. Zha, et. al., <a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2510.04354">&#8220;Reliable and Scalable Robot Policy Evaluation with Imperfect Simulators&#8221;</a></li>
<li><span><span>A. Jindal, D. Kalashnikov, et. al., <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.21651">&#8220;Can AI Perceive Physical Danger and Intervene?&#8221;</a></span></span><span><span></span></span><span><span></span></span></li>
<li><span><span>A. Hancock, X. Wu, et. al., <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.22195">&#8220;Actions as Language: Fine-Tuning VLMs into VLAs Without Catastrophic Forgetting&#8221;</a></span></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Sept&#8217; 25: New tech report from the Gemini Robotics Team:<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.03342"><span><span> &#8220;Gemini Robotics 1.5: Pushing the Frontier of Generalist Robots with Advanced Embodied Reasoning, Thinking, and Motion Transfer&#8221;</span></span></a></li>
